The course discusses the following themes: Overview of scientific information sources. Databases. Principles and strategy of information search. Search in the e-catalogue ESTER and in the Estonian articles databases. Research databases accessible for the University of Tartu. Search in different search environments. Information search on the Internet. Evaluation of the quality of information sources. Avoiding plagiarism.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to offer knowledge and practical skills in searching professional scientific  information from electronic information sources.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the students 
are familiar with information search principles and advanced search techniques and are able to apply them effectively in different search environments;
are familiar with and can successfully use  important research databases and are able to find open access research information on the Internet;
are familiar with and can use the reference manager  Zotero.
